      • printListing

        public static void printListing(java.io.Writer out,
                                java.io.Reader reader,
                                ReportReader reports,
                                java.lang.String sysId,
                                int maxLineLength,
                                boolean lineNumbers,
                                java.lang.String language)
        Print listing of input source line range with error reports to the output stream.
        Parameters:
        out - The output writer.
        reader - The reader with the source.
        reports - reader of messages.
        sysId - Filter source name (sysId), if null no filter.
        maxLineLength - maximal length of printed line (longer lines are wrapped).
        language - Language ID or null (i.e. default).
        lineNumbers - if true then line numbers are printed.

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String... args)
        Main - print error file from command line.
        Parameters:
        args - The array of strings with following structure:

        source [output] [-i n]] [-o]

        where:

        -i errfile ... file name with error records

        -o output ... name of output file (default is standard output)
